This article is a transcript of remarks made by Prime Minister Theresa May and President Donald Trump during a joint press conference at Chequers, Buckinghamshire, England. The leaders discussed various topics including the strong security cooperation between the US and UK, the need to respond to malign state activity and terrorism, economic cooperation and trade agreements, the importance of the transatlantic relationship, and their upcoming meetings with Russian President Vladimir Putin. President Trump also expressed his concerns about immigration in Europe and his desire to improve relations with Russia. Prime Minister May addressed questions about her Brexit plan and her relationship with President Trump.